* =============================================================================
* scheme-agediff.scheme
*
* A clean, minimal Stata graph scheme for the agediff project.
* Builds on the built-in s1color scheme and overrides key settings
* to produce publication-ready, ggplot2 theme_minimal-inspired figures:
*
*   • White backgrounds throughout
*   • No outer plot-region border
*   • Subtle horizontal-only grid lines (light grey, very thin)
*   • Thin, clean axis lines and ticks
*   • Compact, readable legend
*
* Usage (add once at the top of any do-file that produces graphs):
*     set scheme agediff
*
* Stata looks for scheme-<name>.scheme in the working directory and the
* ado path; place this file in the project root (alongside main.do).
* =============================================================================

#include s1color

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Backgrounds — force white everywhere
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
color background          white
color plotregion          white
color matrix_plotregion   white
color legend              white

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Plot-region outer border — remove for a cleaner look
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
yesno draw_plotregion_border  no

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Grid lines — horizontal only, very light grey
* Vertical grid lines add visual clutter; horizontal lines aid reading values
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
yesno draw_major_hgrid    yes
yesno draw_major_vgrid    no
yesno draw_minor_hgrid    no
yesno draw_minor_vgrid    no
color major_grid          "220 220 220"
linewidth major_grid      vthin

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Axis lines and tick marks — keep thin and unobtrusive
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
linewidth axisline        thin
linewidth tick            thin
linewidth minortick       vthin

* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Legend — no box border, compact
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
yesno legend_force_keysym  no
color legend_line          white
